
[1]aphorism

   APH'ORISM, n. [Gr. determination, distinction; from to separate.]

   A maxim; a precept, or principle expressed in few words; a detached
   sentence containing some important truth; as, the aphorisms of
   Hippocrates, or of the civil law.
